{"formatVersion":"1","manifest":{"primaryCategory":"Faith & Devotion","subcategory":"Sufism","audienceTags":["tradition:sufism","theme:love","theme:beauty","audience:meditation"],"sortPriority":28,"groupingLevels":["ghazal"],"groupingLabels":["Ghazal"],"dataPath":"Data/Collections/Hafiz_Divan.json","supplementalDataPath":null,"languageCode":"en","displayNameEnglish":"Hafiz — Divan","script":"Latin","isRTL":false,"transliterationAvailable":false,"contentRating":"devotional","sourceId":"hafizDivan","displayName":"Hafiz — Divan","version":"2.0","language":"English","edition":"Clarke, Bell Translations","type":"quotes","browseOrder":"sequence","itemCount":871,"supportsRandom":true,"supportsBrowse":true},"data":[{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-1","text":"I have come into this world to experience this: men and women who are spiritually alive lighting up like a thousand suns. I have come into this world to see this: the sword drop from men's hands even at the height of their arc of anger.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 1 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"1"},"sequenceIndex":0,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-2","text":"Even after all this time the sun never says to the earth, 'You owe Me.' Look what happens with a love like that — it lights the whole sky.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 2 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"2"},"sequenceIndex":1,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-3","text":"The small man builds cages for everyone he knows. While the sage, who has to duck his head when the moon is low, keeps dropping keys all night long for the beautiful, rowdy prisoners.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 3 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"3"},"sequenceIndex":2,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-4","text":"Fear is the cheapest room in the house. I would like to see you living in better conditions.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 4 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"4"},"sequenceIndex":3,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-5","text":"My dear, poetry is what makes you feel something important is always happening. The best moments in reading are when you come across something which you thought only you knew, or felt.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 5 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"5"},"sequenceIndex":4,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-6","text":"The heart is a thousand-stringed instrument that can only be tuned with love.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 6 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"6"},"sequenceIndex":5,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-7","text":"Stay close to anything that makes you glad you are alive.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 7 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"7"},"sequenceIndex":6,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-8","text":"Carry your heart to the field of surrender. Drop it there. Just drop it all. Your past, your plans, your fears — drop them there.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 8 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"8"},"sequenceIndex":7,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-9","text":"Laugh because that is the purest sound. Live because you can. Love because it is the only thing that brings light.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 9 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"9"},"sequenceIndex":8,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-10","text":"Now is the time to know that all you do is sacred. Now, why not consider a lasting truce with yourself and God?","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 10 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"10"},"sequenceIndex":9,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-11","text":"I am a hole in a flute that the Christ's breath moves through. Listen to this music.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 11 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"11"},"sequenceIndex":10,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-12","text":"All religions, all this singing, is one song. The differences are just illusion and vanity.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 12 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"12"},"sequenceIndex":11,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-13","text":"What a divine restlessness God has given us. Even the stars must move.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 13 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"13"},"sequenceIndex":12,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-14","text":"A wine-house existence is the only noble life: it is the companion of kings and the companion of beggars alike.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 14 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"14"},"sequenceIndex":13,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-15","text":"Find where your joy lives, and live there. Move your soul's house there.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 15 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"15"},"sequenceIndex":14,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-16","text":"Someone who does not run toward the allure of love walks a road where nothing lives.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 16 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"16"},"sequenceIndex":15,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-17","text":"It is all just love letters from God. Everything is a message from the Divine.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 17 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"17"},"sequenceIndex":16,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-18","text":"The great religions are the ships, poets the life boats. Every sane person I know has jumped overboard.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 18 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"18"},"sequenceIndex":17,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-19","text":"When the real music comes, stop all other activities.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 19 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"19"},"sequenceIndex":18,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-20","text":"God wants to manhandle us, lock us inside of a tiny room with Himself and practice His dropkick.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 20 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"20"},"sequenceIndex":19,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-21","text":"The gift of love is a holy mystery — I cannot explain why this world is here, except that it was filled with so much lovingkindness.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 21 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"21"},"sequenceIndex":20,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-22","text":"Your breath is a sacred tool. When you breathe in deeply, you are drinking from the fountain of the infinite.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 22 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"22"},"sequenceIndex":21,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-23","text":"I am in love with every church, and mosque, and temple, and any kind of shrine because I know it is there that people say the different names of the One God.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 23 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"23"},"sequenceIndex":22,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-24","text":"Even after all this time the sun never says to the earth, 'You owe me.' Look what happens with a love like that — it lights the whole sky.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 24 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"24"},"sequenceIndex":23,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-25","text":"Peel open your heart. Do not go to sleep. Stay awake for the one who is returning.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 25 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"25"},"sequenceIndex":24,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-26","text":"Whatever happens, I will keep choosing love.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 26 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"26"},"sequenceIndex":25,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-27","text":"I am like a bird from another continent, sitting in this aviary. The day is coming when I fly off, but who is it now in my ear who hears my voice?","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 27 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"27"},"sequenceIndex":26,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-28","text":"The Beloved is all in all; the lover only veils. The Beloved is living, the lover a dead thing.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 28 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"28"},"sequenceIndex":27,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-29","text":"I die laughing. That is the only kind of death worth dying.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 29 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"29"},"sequenceIndex":28,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ghazal-30","text":"Don't surrender your loneliness so quickly. Let it cut more deep. Let it ferment and season you as few human or even divine ingredients can.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz, Ghazal 30 (Clarke trans.)","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"groups":{"ghazal":"30"},"sequenceIndex":29,"isVerified":true},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000031","text":"Boy, let yon liquid ruby flow,And bid thy pensive heart be glad,Whate’er the frowning zealots say:Tell them, their Eden cannot showA stream so clear as Rocnabad,A bow’r so sweet as Mosellay.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000032","text":"The dimple that thy chin contains has beauty in its round,That never has been fathomed yet by myriad thoughts profound.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000033","text":"Sweet are the garden, the rose, and wine, but they would not be sweet without the company of my darling.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000034","text":"What necessity for a sword to slay the lover, when a glance can deprive him of half his life!","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000035","text":"'Tis writ on Paradise's gate,\"Woe to the dupe that yields to Fate!\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000036","text":"It is a crime to seek to raise but self,Before all other men to praise but self,The pupil of the eye a lesson gives,Be all submitted to thy gaze but self.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000037","text":"What holds in peace this two-fold world, let this two-fold sentence showAmity to every friend, courtesy to every foe.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000038","text":"Learn meekness from the shell in ocean’s bedAnd pearls on one who wounds thy head bestow.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000039","text":"I have shut my eye like a falcon to all the worldSince my (inward) eye is open to thy beauteous countenance.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000040","text":"Though many a rose in this garden is bornNo mortal who culls one escapes from the thorn.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000041","text":"Thy curl is ever drawing the heart silentlyWho hath power to speak (quarrel) with Thy heart-vanishing curl.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000042","text":"Opportunity flies, O brother,As the cloud that quick doth pass;Oh make use of it! life is preciousIf we let it go,—alas!","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000043","text":"Slight me not zealot, go thou hence ashamedFor naught is slight that has by God been framed.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000044","text":"Come! hear of those who have felt sorrow’s touchTheir words are few, but what they mean is much.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000045","text":"What serves thy armour ’gainst Fate’s arrows fierce?What serves thy shield if Destiny transpierce?Though steel and iron may thy ramparts plateWhen comes the mandate, Death shall burst thy gate.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000046","text":"Like are, if void of purity, the k‘aba and the idle-faneThe house that has not chastity can in its walls no good contain.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000047","text":"The meshes of the net are strong but God withholds His grace from none,Not otherwise could man prevail o’er Satan the stone-pelted one.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000048","text":"Wash from the dross of life thy hands as the Path’s men of oldAnd, winning love’s alchemic power, transmute thyself to gold.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000049","text":"How well said the aged farmer to his son,O light of my eyes, thou wilt not reap save that which thou hast sown.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000050","text":"Daughters of turbulent mind awaking their mothers’ ire,And sons who of froward mood wish ill to their sire, I see;Sherbets of sugar and rose the world to the fool supplies,But naught save his own heart’s blood the food of the wise I see;Galled by the pack-saddle’s weight the Arab’s proud steed grows old,Yet always the ass’s neck encircled with gold I see.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000051","text":"Breeze which at the morning blowest,Fly, if faith and truth thou knowest,Say, to my Beloved one turning;He who with thy love is burningDying sighs where he is hidden‘Life without thee is forbidden.’","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","theme:truth","theme:wisdom","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000052","text":"Heart, should the flood of death life’s fabric sweep away,Noah shall steer the ark o’er billows dark, despair not.Though perilous the stage, though out of sight the goal, Whithersoe’er we wend, there is an end, despair not.If love evades our grasp, and rivals press their suit,God, Lord of every change, surveys the range, despair not.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000053","text":"O partridge, bird of graceful gait, say whether wouldst thou shape thy way?Be not so bold, for well we know how the religious cat can pray.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000054","text":"If by the Holy Spirit’s grace the gift again be wonThe works which the Messias wrought by others may be done.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000055","text":"None see nor hear the malice of the skyEach ear is deaf and blind is every eyeOft those who moon and sun their pillow thoughtHave later bricks and clay too gladly sought.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000056","text":"Aloud I say it and with heart of glee,‘Love’s slave am I and from both worlds am free.’Can I, the bird of sacred gardens tell,Into this net of chance how first I fell?","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000057","text":"Enjoy! ’twixt lip and mouth the bounds as nothing areIf humbled, care not; as the rose be gay,Life’s honours which pass soon away, as nothing are.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000058","text":"Regard opportunity. For when uproar fell upon the world,Hafiz struck at the cup and through grief took the corner of retirement.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000059","text":"Profit by companionship; this two-doored house (i.e., life) forsaken,No pathway that can thither lead in future time is taken.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000060","text":"Reckon as plunder the path of profligacy. For this trackLike the path to the hidden treasure is not evident to every one.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000061","text":"A Shah no other than thyself aspiring Hafiz craves;Oh! were he in thy doorway’s dust one of thy common slaves.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000062","text":"If it is thy desire that the Beloved should not break the covenant,Keep thy end of the thread that He may keep his end.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000063","text":"Be misery thy portion here, O Sage, or be it blissRefer it not to other men: ’tis God who orders this.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000064","text":"High birth may be a pearl of lustre, but let thine effort beTo rise by deeds. Distinct is greatness from birth and pedigree.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000065","text":"Spend well thy time; drink wine within the bowerFor when a week is gone, the flower is not;Snatch, snatch the hour that glads the heart so wellFor the pearl always in the shell is not.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000066","text":"And what though all the world should sink! Hafis! with thee, alone with thee Will I contend! joy, misery, The portion of us twain shall be; Like thee to love, like thee to drink,— This be my pride,—this, life to me!","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000067","text":"Herrlich ist der OrientUbers Mittelmeer gedrungen;Nur wer Hafiz liebt und kenntWeiss was Calderon gesungen.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000068","text":"Sir William Jones, A Grammar of the Persian Language (1771) · Poems, Consisting Chiefly of Translations from the Asiatick Languages (1772)","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000069","text":"Herman Bicknell, Hafiz of Shiraz: Selections from his Poems, Translated from the Persian (1875)","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000070","text":"Anonymous, A Century of Ghazels, or, A Hundred Odes, Selected and Translated from the Diwan of Hafiz (1875)","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000071","text":"Claud Field: A Dictionary of Oriental Quotations: Arabic And Persian, The Macmillan Company, 1911. https://archive.org/details/a-dictionary-of-oriental-quotations-arabic-and-persian_202203","author":"Hafiz","source":"Wikiquote","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000072","text":"Produced by Audrey Longhurst, Mary Meehan, and the Online Distributed Proofreading Team.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000073","text":"Author of \"Old Delabole,\" \"Brunel's Tower,\" etc.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000074","text":"NORTHOVER DECIDES XXV THE WOMAN'S DARKNESS XXVI OF HUMAN NATURE XXVII THE MASTER OF THE MILL XXVIII CLASH OF OPINIONS XXIX THE BUNCH OF GRAPES XXX A TRIUMPH OF REASON XXXI THE OFFER DECLINED","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000075","text":"The people were coming to church and one had thought it Sunday, but for two circumstances. The ring of bells at St. Mary's did not peal, and the women were dressed in black as the men.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000076","text":"All were not attired for a funeral.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000077","text":"A small crowd of women, with one or two men among them, stood together where a sycamore threw a patch of shade on a triangular space of grass near the church.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000078","text":"There were fifty of these people--ancient women, others in their prime, and many young maidens.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000079","text":"Some communion linked them and the few men who stood with them.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000080","text":"All wore a black band upon their left arms.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000081","text":"Drab or grey was their attire, but sun-bonnets nodded bright as butterflies among them, and even their dull raiment was more cheerful than the gathering company in black who now began to mass their numbers and crane their heads along the highway.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000082","text":"Bridetown lies near the sea in a valley under a range of grassy downs.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000083","text":"It is the centre of a network of little lanes with cottages dotted upon them, or set back behind small gardens.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000084","text":"The dwellings stood under thatch, or weathered tile, and their faces at this season were radiant with roses and honeysuckles, jasmine and clematis.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000085","text":"Pinks, lilies, columbines made the garden patches gay, and, as though so many flowers were not enough, the windows, too, shone with geraniums and the scarlet tassels of great cactus, that lifted their exotic, thorny bodies behind the window panes.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000086","text":"Not a wall but flaunted red valerian and snapdragon.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000087","text":"Indeed Bridetown was decked with blooms.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000088","text":"Here and there in the midst stood better houses, with some expanse of lawn before them and flat shrubs that throve in that snug vale. Good walnut trees and mulberries threw their shadows on grass plat and house front, while the murmur of bees came from many bright borders.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000089","text":"South the land rose again to the sea cliffs, for the spirits of ocean and the west wind have left their mark upon Bride Vale.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000090","text":"The white gulls float aloft; the village elms are moulded by Zephyr with sure and steady breath.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000091","text":"Of forestal size and unstunted, yet they turn their backs, as it were, upon the west and, yielding to that unsleeping pressure, incline landward.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000092","text":"They congregate in an oasis about Bridetown, then wend away through valley meadows, but leave the green hills bare.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000093","text":"The high ground rolls upward to a gentle skyline and the hillsides, denuded by water springs, or scratched by man, reveal the silver whiteness of the chalk where they are wounded.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000094","text":"Bride river winds in the midst, and her bright waters throw a loop round the eastern frontier of the hamlet, pass under the highway, bring life to the cottage gardens and turn more wheels than one.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000095","text":"Bloom of apple and pear are mirrored on her face and fruit falls into her lap at autumn time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000096","text":"Then westward she flows through the water meadows, and so slips uneventfully away to sea, where the cliffs break and there stretches a little strand.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000097","text":"To the last she is crowned with flowers, and the meadowsweets and violets that decked her cradle give place to sea poppies, sea hollies, and stones encrusted with lichens of red gold, where Bride flows to one great pool, sinks into the sand and glides unseen to her lover.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000098","text":"\"They're coming!\" said one of the crowd; but it was a false alarm.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000099","text":"A flock of breeding lambs of the Dorset horned sheep pattered through the village on their way to pasture.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000100","text":"The young, healthy creatures, with amber-coloured horns and yellow eyes, trotted contentedly along together and left an ovine reek in the air.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mental-health","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000101","text":"Behind them came the shepherd--a high-coloured, middle-aged man with a sharp nose and mild, grey eyes.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000102","text":"He could give news of the funeral, which was on the way behind him.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000103","text":"An iron seat stood under the sycamore on the triangular patch of grass, and a big woman sat upon it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000104","text":"She was of vast dimensions, broad and beamy as a Dutch sloop.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000105","text":"Her bulk was clad in dun colour, and on her black bonnet appeared a layer of yellow dust.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000106","text":"She spoke to others of the little crowd who surrounded her.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000107","text":"They came from Bridetown Spinning Mill, for work was suspended because Henry Ironsyde, the mill owner, had died and now approached his grave.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000108","text":"\"The Ironsydes bury here, but they don't live here,\" said Sally Groves. \"They lived here once, at North Hill House; but that's when I first came to the Mill as a bit of a girl.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000109","text":"The big woman fanned herself with a handkerchief, then spoke a grey man with a full beard, small head, and discontented eyes. He was Levi Baggs, the hackler.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000110","text":"\"We shall have those two blessed boys over us now, no doubt,\" he said. \"But what know they? Things will be as they were, and time and wages the same as before.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000111","text":"\"They'll be sure to do what their father wished, and there was a murmur of changes before he died,\" said Sally Groves; but Levi shook his head.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000112","text":"\"Daniel Ironsyde is built like his father, to let well alone. Raymond Ironsyde don't count. He'll only want his money.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000113","text":"\"Have you ever seen Mr. Raymond?\" asked a girl. She was Nancy Buckler, a spinner--hard-featured, sharp-voiced, and wiry. Nancy might have been any age between twenty-five and forty. She owned to thirty.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000114","text":"\"He don't come to Bridetown, and if you want to see him, you must go to 'The Tiger,' at Bridport,\" declared another girl. Her name was Sarah Northover.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000115","text":"\"My Aunt Nelly keeps 'The Seven Stars,' in Barrack Street,\" she explained, \"and that's just alongside 'The Tiger,' and my Aunt Nelly's very friendly with Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000116","text":"Gurd, of 'The Tiger,' and he's told her that Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000117","text":"Raymond is there half his time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000118","text":"He's all for sport and such like, and 'The Tiger's' a very sporting house.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000119","text":"\"He won't be no good to the mills if he's that sort,\" prophesied Sally Groves.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000120","text":"\"I saw him once, with another young fellow called Motyer,\" answered Sarah Northover. \"He's very good-looking--fair and curly--quite different from Mr. Daniel.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000121","text":"\"Light or dark, they're Henry Ironsyde's sons and be brought up in his pattern no doubt,\" declared Mr. Baggs.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000122","text":"People continued to appear, and among them walked an elderly man, a woman and a girl.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000123","text":"Ernest Churchouse, of 'The Magnolias,' with his widowed housekeeper, Mary Dinnett, and her daughter, Sabina.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000124","text":"The girl was nineteen, dark and handsome, and very skilled in her labour.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000125","text":"None disputed her right to be called first spinner at the mills.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000126","text":"She was an impulsive, ambitious maiden, and Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000127","text":"Best, foreman at the works, claimed for her that she brought genius as well as understanding to her task.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000128","text":"Sabina joined her friend, Nancy Buckler; Mrs.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000129","text":"Dinnett, who had been a mill hand in her youth, took a seat beside Sally Groves, and Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000130","text":"He was a round-faced, clean-shaven man with mild, grey eyes and iron grey hair.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000131","text":"His shoulders were high, and his legs short.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000132","text":"Walking irked him, for a sedentary life and hearty appetite had made him stout.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000133","text":"The fall of Henry Ironsyde served somewhat to waken Ernest Churchouse from the placid dream in which he lived, shake him from his normal quietude, and remind him of the flight of time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000134","text":"He and the dead man were of an age and had been boys together.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000135","text":"Their fathers founded the Bridetown Spinning Mill, and when the elder men passed away, it was Henry Ironsyde who took over the enterprise and gradually bought out Ernest Churchouse.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000136","text":"But while Ironsyde left Bridetown and lived henceforth at Bridport, that he might develop further interests in the spinning trade, Ernest had been well content to remain there, enjoy his regular income and live at 'The Magnolias,' his father's old-world house, beside the river.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000137","text":"His tastes were antiquarian and literary.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000138","text":"He wrote when in the mood, and sometimes read papers at the Mechanics' Institute of Bridport.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000139","text":"But he was constitutionally averse from real work of any sort, lacked ambition, and found all the fame he needed in the village community with which his life had been passed.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000140","text":"Churchouse strolled now into the churchyard to look at the grave.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000141","text":"It opened beside that of Henry Ironsyde's parents and his wife.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000142","text":"She had been dead for fifteen years.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000143","text":"A little crowd peered down into the green-clad pit, for the sides, under the direction of John Best, had been lined with cypress and bay.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000144","text":"The grass was rank, but it had been mown down for this occasion round the tombs of the Ironsydes, though elsewhere darnel rose knee deep and many venerable stones slanted out of it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000145","text":"Immediately south of the churchyard wall stood the Mill, and Benny Cogle, engineman at the works, who now greeted Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000146","text":"Churchouse, dwelt on the fact.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000147","text":"\"Morning, sir,\" he said, \"a brave day for the funeral, sure enough.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000148","text":"\"Good morning, Benny,\" answered the other. His voice was weak and gentle.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000149","text":"\"When I think how near the church and Mill do lie together, I have thoughts,\" continued Benny. He was a florid man of thirty, with tow-coloured hair and blue eyes.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000150","text":"\"Naturally. You work and pray here all inside a space of fifty yards. But for my part, Benny Cogle, I am inclined to think that working is the best form of praying.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000151","text":"Mr. Churchouse always praised work for others and, indeed, was under the impression that he did his share.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000152","text":"\"Same here,\" replied the engineman, \"especially while you're young.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000153","text":"Anyway, if I had to choose between 'em, I'd sooner work.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000154","text":"'Tis better for the mind and appetite.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000155","text":"Ironsyde, when he lies down there, could tell the truth, he'd rather be hearing the Mill going six days a week and feeling his grave throbbing to my engines, than list to the sound of the church organ on the seventh.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:truth","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000156","text":"\"Not so,\" reproved Mr. Churchouse. \"We must not go so far as that. Henry Ironsyde was a God-fearing man and respected the Sabbath as we all should, and most of us do.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000157","text":"\"The weaker vessels come to church, I grant,\" said Benny, \"but the men be after more manly things than church-going of a Sunday nowadays.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000158","text":"\"So much the worse for them,\" declared Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000159","text":"\"Here,\" he continued, \"there are naturally more women than men.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000160","text":"Since my father and Henry Ironsyde's father established these mills, which are now justly famous in the county, the natural result has happened and women have come here in considerable numbers.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000161","text":"Women preponderate in spinning places, because the work of spinning yarn has always been in their hands from time immemorial.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000162","text":"And they tend our modern machinery as deftly as of old they twirled the distaff and worked the spinning-wheel; and as steadily as they used to trudge the rope walks and spin, like spiders, from the masses of flax or hemp at their waists.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000163","text":"\"The females want religion without a doubt,\" said Benny.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000164","text":"\"I'm tokened to Mercy Gale, for instance; she looks after the warping wheels, and if that girl didn't say her prayers some fine morning, she'd be as useless as if she hadn't eat her breakfast.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:christianity","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000165","text":"'Tis the feminine nature that craves for support.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000166","text":"A very old man stood and peered into the grave. He was the father of Levi Baggs, the hackler, and people said he was never seen except on the occasion of a funeral. The ancient had been reduced to a mere wisp by the attrition of time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000167","text":"He put his hand on the arm of Mr. Churchouse and regarded the grave with a nodding head.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000168","text":"\"Ah, my dear soul,\" he said. \"Life, how short--eternity, how long!\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000169","text":"\"And I ask myself, as each corpse goes in, how many more pits will open afore mine.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000170","text":"\"'Tis hid with your Maker, William.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000171","text":"\"Thank God I'm a good old man and ripe and ready,\" said Mr. Baggs. \"Not,\" he added, \"that there's any credit to me; for you can't be anything much but good at ninety-two.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000172","text":"\"While the brain is spared we can think evil, William.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000173","text":"\"Not a brain like mine, I do assure 'e.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000174","text":"A little girl ran into the churchyard--a pretty, fair child, whose bright hair contrasted with the black she wore.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000175","text":"\"They have come and father sent me to tell you, Mr. Churchouse,\" she said.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000176","text":"\"Thank you, Estelle,\" he answered, and they returned to the open space together. The child then joined her father, and Mr. Churchouse, saluting the dead, walked to the first mourning coach and opened the door.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000177","text":"It was a heavy and solid funeral of Victorian fashion proper to the time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000178","text":"The hearse had been drawn by four black horses with black trappings, and over the invisible coffin nodded a gloomy harvest of black ostrich plumes.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000179","text":"There were no flowers, and some children, who crept forward with a little wreath of wild roses, were pushed back.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000180","text":"The men from the Mill helped to carry their master into the church; but there were not enough of them to support the massive oak that held a massive man, and John Best, Levi Baggs, Benny Cogle and Nicholas Roberts were assisted by the undertakers.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000181","text":"From the first coach descended an elderly woman and a youth.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000182","text":"The lady was Miss Jenny Ironsyde, sister of the dead, and with her came her nephew Daniel, the new mill-owner.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000183","text":"He was five-and-twenty--a sallow, strong-faced young fellow, broad in the shoulder and straight in the back.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000184","text":"His eyes were brown and steady, his mouth and nose indicated decision; the funeral had not changed his cast of countenance, which was always solemn; for, as his father before him, he lacked a sense of humour.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000185","text":"Mr. Churchouse shook hands and peered into the coach.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000186","text":"\"Not come,\" answered Miss Ironsyde. She was a sturdy woman of five-and-fifty, with a pleasant face and kindly eyes. But they were clouded now and she showed agitation.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000187","text":"\"Not come!\" exclaimed Ernest with very genuine consternation.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000188","text":"Daniel Ironsyde answered. His voice was slow, but he had a natural instinct for clarity and spoke more to the point than is customary with youth.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000189","text":"\"My brother has not come because my father has left him out of his will, Mr. Churchouse.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000190","text":"\"Absolutely. Will you take my aunt's arm and follow next after me, please?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000191","text":"Two clergymen met the coffin at the lich-gate, and behind the chief mourners came certain servants and dependents, followed by the women of the Mill.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000192","text":"Then a dozen business men walked together.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000193","text":"A few of his co-workers had sent their carriages; but most came themselves, to do the last honour to one greatly respected.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000194","text":"Mr. Churchouse paid little attention to the obsequies.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000195","text":"\"Not at his father's funeral!\" he kept thinking to himself. His simple mind was thrown into a large confusion by such an incident. The fact persisted rather than the reason for it. He longed to learn more, but could not until the funeral was ended.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:resilience","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000196","text":"When the coffin came to the grave, Mary Dinnett stole home to look after the midday dinner.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000197","text":"It had weighed on her mind since she awoke, for Miss Ironsyde and Daniel were coming to 'The Magnolias' to partake of a meal before returning home.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000198","text":"There were no relations from afar to be considered, and no need for funeral baked meats in the dead man's house.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000199","text":"When all was ended and only old William Baggs stood by the grave and watched the sextons fill it, a small company walked together up the hill north of Bridetown.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000200","text":"Churchouse, and behind them followed Miss Jenny Ironsyde with a man and a child.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000201","text":"The man rented North Hill House.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000202","text":"Arthur Waldron was a widower, who lived now for two things: his little daughter, Estelle, and sport.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000203","text":"No other considerations challenged his mind.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:resilience","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000204","text":"He knew that his little girl had brains, and he dealt fairly with her in the matter of education.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000205","text":"Of the Ironsyde brothers, Raymond was his personal friend, and Mr. Waldron now permitted himself some vague expression of regret that the young man should have been absent on such an occasion.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000206","text":"\"Yes,\" said Miss Ironsyde, to whom he spoke, \"if there's any excuse for convention it's at a funeral.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000207","text":"No doubt people will magnify the incident into a scandal--for their own amusement and the amusement of their friends.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000208","text":"If Raymond had enjoyed time to reflect, I feel sure he would have come; but there was no time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000209","text":"His father has made no provision for him, and he is rather upset.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000210","text":"It is not unnatural that he should be, for dear Henry, while always very impatient of Raymond's sporting tastes and so on, never threatened anything like this.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000211","text":"\"No doubt Mr. Ironsyde would have made a difference if he had not died so suddenly.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000212","text":"\"I think so too,\" she answered.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000213","text":"Then Waldron and his daughter went homewards; while the others, turning down a lane to the right, reached 'The Magnolias'--a small, ancient house whose face was covered with green things and whose lawn spread to the river bank.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000214","text":"Mrs. Dinnett had prepared a special meal of a sort associated with the mournful business of the day; for a funeral feast has its own character; the dishes should be cold and the wine should be white or brown.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000215","text":"Mr. Churchouse was concerned to know what Daniel meant to do for Raymond; but he found the heir by no means inclined to emotional generosity.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000216","text":"Daniel spoke in a steady voice, though he showed a spark of feeling presently. The fire, however, was for his dead father, not his living brother.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000217","text":"\"I'm very sorry that Raymond could have been so small as to keep away from the funeral,\" he said. \"It was petty. But, as Aunt Jenny says, he's built like that, and no doubt the shock of being ignored knocked him off his balance.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000218","text":"\"He has the defects of his qualities, my dear.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000219","text":"The same people can often rise to great heights and sink to great depths.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000220","text":"They can do worse things--and better things--than we humdrum folk, who jog along the middle of the road.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000221","text":"We must forgive such people for doing things we wouldn't do, and remember their power to do things we couldn't do.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000222","text":"The young man was frankly puzzled by this speech, which came from his aunt. He shrugged his shoulders.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000223","text":"\"I've got to think of father first and Raymond afterwards,\" he said.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000224","text":"\"I owe my first duty to my father, who trusted me and honoured me, and knew very well that I should obey his wishes and carry on with my life as he would have liked to see me.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000225","text":"He has made a very definite and clear statement, and I should be disloyal to him--dishonest to him--if I did anything contrary to the spirit of it.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:truth","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000226","text":"\"Who would wish you to?\" asked Ernest Churchouse.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000227","text":"\"But a brother is a brother,\" he continued, \"and since there is nothing definite about Raymond in the will, you should, I think, argue like this.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000228","text":"You should say to yourself, 'my father was disappointed with my brother and did not know what to do about him; but, having a high opinion of me and my good sense and honesty, he left my brother to my care.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","theme:truth","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000229","text":"He regarded me, in fact, as my brother's keeper, and hoped that I would help Raymond to justify his existence.' Don't you feel like that?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000230","text":"\"I feel that my father was very long-suffering with Raymond, and his will tells me that he had a great deal more to put up with from Raymond than anybody ever knew, except my brother himself.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000231","text":"\"You needn't take up the cudgels for your father, Dan,\" interposed Miss Ironsyde.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000232","text":"\"Be sure that your dear father, from the peace which now he enjoys, would not like to see you make his quarrel with Raymond your quarrel.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000233","text":"I'm not extenuating Raymond's selfish and unthinking conduct as a son.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000234","text":"His own conscience will exact the payment for wrong done beyond repair.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000235","text":"But he's your brother, not your son; and you must ask yourself, whether as a brother, you've fairly got any quarrel with him.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000236","text":"Daniel considered a moment, then he spoke.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000237","text":"\"I have not,\" he said--\"except the general quarrel that he's a waster and not justifying his existence. We have had practically nothing to do with each other since we left school.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000238","text":"\"Well,\" declared Mr. Churchouse, \"now you must have something to do with each other. It is an admirable thought of your Aunt Jenny's that your father has honoured your judgment by leaving the destiny of Raymond more or less in your hands.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000239","text":"\"I didn't say that; you said it,\" interrupted the lady. \"Raymond's destiny is in his own hands. But I do feel, of course, that Daniel can't ignore him. The moment has come when a strong effort must be made to turn Raymond into a useful member of society.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000240","text":"\"What allowance did dear Henry make him?\" asked Mr. Churchouse.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000241","text":"\"Father gave him two hundred a year, and father paid all his debts before his twenty-first birthday; but he didn't pay them again. Raymond has told Aunt Jenny that he's owing two hundred pounds at this moment.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000242","text":"\"And nothing to show for it--we may be sure of that. Well, it might have been worse. Is the allowance to be continued?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000243","text":"\"No,\" said Miss Ironsyde. \"That's the point. It is to cease. Henry expressly directs that it is to cease; and to me that is very significant.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000244","text":"\"Of course, for it shows that he leaves Raymond in his brother's hands.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000245","text":"\"I have heard Henry say that Raymond beat him,\" continued Miss Ironsyde.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000246","text":"\"He was a good father and a forgiving father, but temperamentally he was not built to understand Raymond.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000247","text":"Some people develop slowly and remain children much longer than other people.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000248","text":"Daniel, like my dear brother before him, has developed quickly and come to man's estate and understanding.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000249","text":"\"His father could trust his eldest son,\" declared Mr. Churchouse, \"and, as I happen to know, Daniel, you always spoke with patience and reason about Raymond--your father has told me so. It was natural and wise, therefore, that my late dear friend should have left Raymond to you.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:relationships","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000250","text":"\"I only want to do my duty,\" said the young man.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000251","text":"\"By stopping away to-day Raymond hasn't made me feel any kinder to him, and if he were not so stupid in some ways, he must have known it would be so; but I am not going to let that weigh against him.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000252","text":"How do you read the fact that my father directs Raymond's allowance to cease, Uncle Ernest?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000253","text":"Mr. Churchouse bore no real connection to the Ironsydes; but his relations had always been close and cordial after he relinquished his share in the business of the mills, and the younger generation was brought up to call him 'uncle.'","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000254","text":"\"I read it like this,\" answered the elder.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000255","text":"\"It means that Raymond is to look to you in future, and that henceforth you may justly demand that he should not live in idleness.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000256","text":"There is nothing more demoralising for youth than to live upon money it doesn't earn.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000257","text":"I should say--subject to your aunt's opinion, to which I attach the greatest importance--that it is your place to give your brother an interest in life and to show him, what you know already, the value and dignity of work.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000258","text":"\"I entirely agree,\" said Jenny Ironsyde. \"I can go further and declare from personal knowledge that my brother had shadowed the idea in his mind.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000259","text":"\"Then leave it there,\" he bade them, \"leave it there and I'll think it out. My father was the fairest man I ever met, and I'll try and be as fair. It's up to Raymond more than me.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000260","text":"\"You can bring a horse to the water, though you can't make him drink,\" admitted Mr. Churchouse. \"But if you bring your horse to the water, you've done all that reason and sense may ask you to do.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000261","text":"Miss Ironsyde, from larger knowledge of the circumstances, felt disposed to carry the question another step. She opened her mouth and drew in her breath to speak--making that little preliminary sound only audible when nothing follows it. But she did not speak.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000262","text":"\"Come into the garden and see Magnolia grandiflora,\" said Mr. Churchouse. \"There are twelve magnificent blossoms open this morning, and I should have picked every one of them for my dear friend's grave, only the direction was clear, that there were to be no flowers.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000263","text":"\"Henry disliked any attempt to soften the edges at such a time,\" explained the dead man's sister.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000264","text":"\"He held that death was the skeleton at the feast of life--a wholesome and stark reminder to the thoughtless living that the grave is the end of our mortal days.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000265","text":"He liked a funeral to be a funeral--black--black.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000266","text":"He did not want the skeleton at the feast to be decked in roses and lilies.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000267","text":"\"An opinion worthy of all respect,\" declared Mr. Churchouse.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000268","text":"Then he asked after the health of his guest and expressed sympathy for her sorrow and great loss.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:grief","theme:love","theme:mental-health","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000269","text":"\"He'd been so much better lately that it was a shock,\" she said, \"but he died as he wanted to die--as all Ironsydes do die--without an illness. It is a tradition that never seems to fail. That reconciled us in a way. And you--how are you? You seldom come to Bridport nowadays.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000270","text":"Mr. Churchouse rarely talked about himself.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000271","text":"\"True. I have been immersed in literary work and getting on with my _magnum opus_: 'The Church Bells of Dorset.' You see one does not obtain much help here--no encouragement. Not that I expect it. We men of letters have to choose between being hermits, or humbugs.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:courage","theme:love","theme:resilience","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000272","text":"\"I always thought a hermit was a humbug,\" said Jenny, smiling for the first time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000273","text":"When I say 'hermit,' I mean 'recluse.' With all the will to be a social success and identify myself with the welfare of the place in which I dwell, my powers are circumscribed.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000274","text":"Do not think I put myself above the people, or pretend any intellectual superiority, or any nonsense of that sort.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000275","text":"No, it is merely a question of time and energy.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000276","text":"My antiquarian work demands both, and so I am deprived by duty from mixing in the social life as much as I wish.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000277","text":"This is not, perhaps, understood, and so I get a character for aloofness, which is not wholly deserved.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000278","text":"\"Don't worry,\" said Miss Ironsyde. \"Everybody cares for you. People don't think about us and our doings half as much as we are prone to fancy. I liked your last article in the _Bridport Gazette_. Only I seemed to have read most of it before.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000279","text":"\"Probably you have. The facts, of course, were common property. My task is to collect data and retail them in a luminous and illuminating way.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000280","text":"He looked away, where Daniel stood by himself with his hands in his pockets and his eyes on the river.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000281","text":"\"A great responsibility for one so young; but he will rise to it.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000282","text":"\"D'you mean his brother, or the Mill?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000283","text":"\"Both,\" answered Ernest Churchouse. \"Both.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000284","text":"Mrs. Dinnett came down the garden.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000285","text":"\"The mourning coach is at the door,\" she said.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000286","text":"\"Daniel insisted that we went home in a mourning coach,\" explained Miss Ironsyde. \"He felt the funeral was not ended until we returned home. That shows imagination, so you can't say he hasn't got any.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000287","text":"\"You can never say anybody hasn't got anything,\" declared Mr. Churchouse. \"Human nature defeats all calculations. The wisest only generalise about it.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000288","text":"The municipal borough of Bridport stretches itself luxuriously from east to west beneath a wooded hill.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000289","text":"Southward the land slopes to broad water-meadows where rivers meet and Brit and Asker wind to the sea.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000290","text":"Evidences of the great local industry are not immediately apparent; but streamers and wisps of steam scattered above the red-tiled roofs tell of work, and westward, where the land falls, there stand shoulder to shoulder the busy mills.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000291","text":"From single yarn that a child could break, to hawsers strong enough to hold a battleship, Bridport meets every need. Her twines and cords and nets are famous the world over; her ropes, cables, cablets and canvas rigged the fleet that scattered the Spanish Armada.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000292","text":"The broad streets with deep, unusual side-walks are a sign of Bridport's past, for they tell of the days when men and women span yarn before their doors, and rope-walks ran their amber and silver threads of hemp and flax along the pavements.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000293","text":"But steel and steam have taken the place of the hand-spinners, though their industry has left its sign-manual upon the township.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000294","text":"For the great, open side-walks make for distinction and spaciousness, and there shall be found in all Dorset, no brighter, cheerfuller place than this.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000295","text":"Bridport's very workhouse, south-facing and bowered in green, blinks half a hundred windows amiably at the noonday sun and helps to soften the life-failure of those who dwell therein.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000296","text":"Off Barrack Street it stands, and at the time of the terror, when Napoleon threatened, soldiers hived here and gave the way its name.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000297","text":"Behind the counter stood Richard Gurd, a middle-aged, broad-shouldered publican with a large and clean-shaven face, heavy-jaw, rather sulky eyes and mighty hands.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000298","text":"\"The usual,\" said the visitor. \"Ray been here?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000299","text":"\"No, Mr. Ned--nor likely to. They're burying his father this morning.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000300","text":"The publican poured out a glass of cherry brandy as he spoke and Mr. Neddy Motyer rolled a cigarette.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000301","text":"\"Ray ain't going,\" said the customer.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000302","text":"\"Not going to his father's funeral!\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000303","text":"\"For a very good reason, too; he's cut off with a shilling.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000304","text":"\"Dear, dear,\" said Mr. Gurd. \"That's bad news, though perhaps not much of a surprise to Mr. Raymond.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000305","text":"\"It's a devil of a lesson to the rising generation,\" declared the youth.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000306","text":"\"To think our own fathers can do such blackguard things, just because they don't happen to like our way of life.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000307","text":"What would become of England if every man was made in the pattern of his father?","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000308","text":"Don't education and all that count?","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000309","text":"If my father was to do such a thing--but he won't; he's too fond of the open air and sport and that.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000310","text":"\"Young men don't study their fathers enough in this generation, however,\" argued the innkeeper, \"nor yet do young women study their mothers enough.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000311","text":"\"We've got to go out in the world and play our parts,\" declared Neddy. \"'Tis for them to study us--not us them. You must have progress. The thing for parents to do is to know they're back numbers and act according.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000312","text":"\"They do--most of them,\" answered Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000313","text":"\"A back number is a back number and behaves as such.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000314","text":"The point for parents is not to forget what it feels like to be young.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000315","text":"That I never have, and you young gentlemen would very soon remind me if I did.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000316","text":"Henry Ironsyde found no time for all-round wisdom.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000317","text":"He poured his brains into hemp and jute and such like.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000318","text":"Why, he didn't even make a minute to court and wed till he was forty-five year old.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000319","text":"And the result of that was that when his brace of boys was over twenty, he stood in sight of seventy and could only see life at that angle.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000320","text":"And what made it worse was, that his eldest, Mister Daniel, was cut just in his own pattern.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000321","text":"So the late gentleman never could forgive Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000322","text":"Raymond for being cut in another pattern.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000323","text":"But if what you say is right and Mister Raymond has been left out in the cold, then I think he's been badly used.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000324","text":"\"So he has--it's a damned shame,\" said Mr. Motyer, \"and I hope Ray will do something about it.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000325","text":"\"There's very little we can do against the writing of the dead,\" answered Mr. Gurd. Then he saluted a man who bustled into the bar.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000326","text":"\"Morning, Job. What's the trouble?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000327","text":"Job Legg was very tall and thin.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000328","text":"He dropped at the middle, but showed vitality and energy in his small face and rodent features.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000329","text":"His hair was black, and his thin mouth and chin clean-shaven.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000330","text":"His eyes were small and very shrewd; his manner was humble.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000331","text":"He had a monotonous inflection and rather chanted in a minor key than spoke.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000332","text":"\"Mrs. Northover's compliments and might we have the big fish kettle till to-morrow? A party have been sprung on us, and five-and-twenty sit down to lunch in the pleasure gardens at two o'clock.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000333","text":"\"And welcome, Job. Go round to the kitchen, will 'e?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000334","text":"Job disappeared and Mr. Gurd explained.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000335","text":"\"My good neighbour at 'The Seven Stars'--her with the fine pleasure gardens and swings and so on.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000336","text":"Her husband's right hand while he lived, and now hers.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000337","text":"I have the use of their stable-yard market days, for their custom is different from mine.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000338","text":"A woman's house and famous for her meat teas and luncheons.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000339","text":"She does very well and deserves to.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000340","text":"\"That old lady with the yellow wig?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000341","text":"\"To you she might seem old, I suppose.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000342","text":"That's the spirit that puts a bit of a strain on the middle-aged and makes such men as me bring home to ourselves what we said and thought when we were young.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000343","text":"'Tis just the natural, thoughtless insolence of youth to say Nelly Northover's an old woman--her being perhaps eight-and-forty.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000344","text":"And to call her hair a wig, because she's fortified it with home-grown what's fallen out over a period of twenty years, is again only the insolence of youth.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000345","text":"One can only say 'forgive 'em, for they know not what they do.'\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000346","text":"\"Well, get me another brandy anyway.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000347","text":"Then entered Raymond Ironsyde, and Mr. Gurd for once felt genuinely sorry to see his customer.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000348","text":"The young man was handsome with large, luminous, grey eyes, curly, brown hair and a beautiful mouth, clean cut, full, firm and finely modelled in the lips.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:beauty","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000349","text":"His nose was straight, high in the nostril and sensitive.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000350","text":"He resembled his brother, Daniel, but stood three inches taller, and his brow was fuller and loftier.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000351","text":"His expression in repose appeared frank and receptive; but to-day his face wore a look half anxious, half ferocious.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000352","text":"He was clad in tweed knickerbockers and a Norfolk jacket, of different pattern but similar material.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000353","text":"His tie was light blue and fastened with a gold pin modelled in the shape of a hunting-horn.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000354","text":"He bore no mark of mourning whatever.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:grief","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000355","text":"\"Whiskey and soda, Gurd. Morning, Neddy.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000356","text":"He spoke defiantly, as though knowing his entrance was a challenge. Then he flung himself down on a cushioned seat in the bow window of the bar-room and took a pipe and tobacco pouch from his pocket.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:resilience","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000357","text":"Mr. Gurd brought the drink round to Raymond. He spoke upon some general subject and pretended to no astonishment that the young man should be here on this day. But the customer cut him short. There was only one subject for discussion in his mind.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000358","text":"\"I suppose you thought I should go to my father's funeral? No doubt, you'll say, with everybody else, that it's a disgrace I haven't.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000359","text":"\"I shall mind my own business and say nothing, Mister Raymond. It's your affair, not ours.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000360","text":"\"I'd have done the same, Ray, if I'd been treated the same,\" said Neddy Motyer.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000361","text":"\"It's a protest,\" explained Raymond Ironsyde. \"To have gone, after being publicly outraged like this in my father's will, was impossible to anybody but a cur. He ignored me as his son, and so I ignore him as my father; and who wouldn't?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000362","text":"\"I suppose Daniel will come up to the scratch all right?\" hazarded Motyer.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000363","text":"\"He'll make some stuffy suggestion, no doubt. He can't see me in the gutter very well.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000364","text":"\"You must get to work, Mr. Raymond; and I can tell you, as one who knows, that work's only dreaded by them who have never done any. You'll soon find that there's nothing better for the nerves and temper than steady work.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000365","text":"Neddy chaffed Mr. Gurd's sentiments and Raymond said nothing. He was looking in front of him, his mind occupied with personal problems.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000366","text":"Neddy Motyer made another encouraging suggestion.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000367","text":"\"There's your aunt, Miss Ironsyde,\" he said. \"She's got plenty of cash, I've heard people say, and she gives tons away in charity. How do you stand with her?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000368","text":"\"Mind your own business, Ned.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000369","text":"\"Sorry,\" answered the other promptly. \"Only wanted to buck you up.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000370","text":"\"I'm not in need of any bucking up, thanks. If I've got to work, I'm quite equal to it. I've got more brains than Daniel, anyway. I'm quite conscious of that.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000371","text":"\"You've got tons more mind than him,\" declared Neddy.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000372","text":"\"And if that's the case, I could do more good, if I chose, than ever Daniel will.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000373","text":"\"Or more harm,\" warned Mr. Gurd. \"Always remember that, Mister Raymond. The bigger the intellects, the more power for wrong as well as right.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000374","text":"\"He'll ask me to go into the works, I expect. And I may, or I may not.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000375","text":"\"I should,\" advised Neddy. \"Bridetown is a very sporting place and you'd be alongside your pal, Arthur Waldron.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000376","text":"\"Don't go to Bridetown with an idea of sport, however--don't do that, Mister Raymond,\" warned Richard Gurd. \"If you go, you put your back into the work and master the business of the Mill.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000377","text":"The young men wasted an hour in futile talk and needless drinking while Gurd attended to other customers. Then Raymond Ironsyde accepted an invitation to return home with Motyer, who lived at Eype, a mile away.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000378","text":"\"I'm going to give my people a rest to-day,\" said Raymond as he departed. \"I shall come in here for dinner, Dick.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000379","text":"\"Very good, sir,\" answered Mr. Gurd; but he shook his head when the young men had gone.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000380","text":"Others in the bar hummed on the subject of young Ironsyde after his back was turned. A few stood up for him and held that he had been too severely dealt with; but the majority and those who knew most about him thought that his ill-fortune was deserved.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000381","text":"\"For look at it,\" said a tradesman, who knew the facts.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000382","text":"\"If he'd been left money, he'd have only wasted the lot in sporting and been worse off after than before; but now he's up against work, and work may be the saving of him.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000383","text":"And if he won't work, let him die the death and get off the earth and make room for a better man.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:mortality","theme:nature","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000384","text":"None denied the honourable obligation to work for every responsible human being.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000385","text":"The warehouse of Bridetown Mill adjoined the churchyard wall and its northern windows looked down upon the burying ground.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000386","text":"The store came first and then the foreman's home, a thatched dwelling bowered in red and white roses, with the mill yard in front and a garden behind.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000387","text":"From these the works were separated by the river.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000388","text":"Bride came by a mill race to do her share, and a water wheel, conserving her strength, took it to the machinery.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:resilience","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000389","text":"For Benny Cogle's engine was reinforced by the river.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000390","text":"Then, speeding forward, Bride returned to her native bed, which wound through the valley south of the works.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000391","text":"A bridge crossed the river from the yard and communicated with the mills--a heterogeneous pile of dim, dun colours and irregular roofs huddled together with silver-bright excrescences of corrugated iron.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000392","text":"A steady hum and drone as of some gigantic beehive ascended from the mills, and their combined steam and water power produced a tremor of earth and a steady roar in the air; while a faint dust storm often flickered about the entrance ways.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000393","text":"The store-house reeked with that fat, heavy odour peculiar to hemp and flax.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000394","text":"It was a lofty building of wide doors and few windows.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000395","text":"Here in the gloom lay bales and stacks of raw material.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000396","text":"Italy, Russia, India, had sent their scutched hemp and tow to Bridetown.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000397","text":"Some was in the rough; the dressed line had already been hackled and waited in bundles of long hemp composed of wisps, or 'stricks' like horses' tails.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000398","text":"The silver and amber of the material made flashes of brightness in the dark storerooms and drew the light to their shining surfaces.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000399","text":"Tall, brown posts supported the rafters, and in the twilight that reigned here, a man moved among the bales piled roof-high around him.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000400","text":"He was gathering rough tow from a broken bale of Russian hemp and had stripped the Archangel matting from the mass.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000401","text":"Levi Baggs, the hackler, proceeded presently to weigh his material and was taking it over the bridge to the hackling shop when he met John Best, the foreman. They stopped to speak, and Levi set down the barrow that bore his load.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000402","text":"\"I see you with him, yesterday. Did you get any ideas out of the man?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000403","text":"Baggs referred to the new master and John Best understood.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000404","text":"\"In a manner of speaking, yes,\" he said. \"Nothing definite, of course. It's too soon to talk of changes, even if Mister Daniel means them. He'll carry on as before for the present, and think twice and again before he does anything different from his father.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000405","text":"\"'Tis just Bridetown luck if he's the sort to keep at a dead parent's apron-strings,\" grumbled the other. \"Nowadays, what with education and so on, the rising generation is generally ahead of the last and moves according.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000406","text":"\"You can move two ways--backward as well as forward,\" answered Best. \"Better he should go on as we've been going, than go back.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000407","text":"\"He daren't go back--the times won't let him. The welfare of the workers is the first demand on capital nowadays. If it weren't, labour would very soon know the reason why.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:courage","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000408","text":"Mr. Best regarded Levi without admiration.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000409","text":"\"You are a grumbler born,\" he said, \"and so fond of it that you squeal before you're hurt, just for the pleasure of squealing.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000410","text":"One thing I can tell you, for Mister Daniel said it in so many words: he's the same in politics as his father; and that's Liberal; and since the Liberals of yesterday are the Radicals of to-morrow, we have every reason to suppose he'll move with the times.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000411","text":"\"We all know what that means,\" answered Mr. Baggs. \"It means getting new machinery and increasing the output of the works for the benefit of the owners, not them that run the show. I don't set no store on a man being a Radical nowadays. You can't trust nobody under a Socialist.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000412","text":"\"You wait till they've got the power, and you'll find that the whip will fall just as heavy from their hands as the masters of to-day.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000413","text":"Better to get small money and be free, than get more and go a slave in state clothes, on state food, in a state house, with a state slave-driver to see you earn your state keep and take your state holidays when the state wills, and work as much or as little as the state pleases.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000414","text":"What you chaps call 'liberty' you'll find is something quite different, Baggs, for it means good-bye to privacy in the home and independence outside it.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000415","text":"\"That's a false and wicked idea of progress, John Best, and well you know it,\" answered Levi.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000416","text":"\"You're one of the sort content to work on a chain and bring up your children likewise; but you can't stand between the human race and freedom--no more can Daniel Ironsyde, or any other man.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000417","text":"\"Well, meantime, till the world's put right by your friends, you get on with your hackling, my old bird, else you'll have the spreaders grumbling,\" answered Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000418","text":"Then he went into his home and Levi trundled the wheelbarrow to a building with a tar-pitched, penthouse roof, which stuck out from the side of the mill, like a fungus on a tree stem.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000419","text":"Within, before a long, low window, stood the hand dresser's tools--two upturned boards set with a mass of steel pins.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000420","text":"The larger board had tall teeth disposed openly; upon the smaller, the teeth were shorter and as dense as a hair brush.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000421","text":"In front of them opened a grating and above ran an endless band.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000422","text":"Behind this grille was an exhaust, which sucked away the dust and countless atoms of vegetable matter scattered by Levi's activities, and the running band from above worked it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000423","text":"For the authorities, he despised, considered the operations of Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000424","text":"Baggs and ordained that they should be conducted under healthy conditions.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mental-health","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000425","text":"He took his seat now before the rougher's hackle, turned up his shirt sleeves over a pair of sinewy arms and powerful wrists and set to work.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000426","text":"From the mass of hemp tow he drew hanks and beat the pins with them industriously, wrenched the mass through the steel teeth again and again and separated the short fibre from the long.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000427","text":"Presently in his hand emerged a wisp of bright fibre, and now flogging the finer hackling board, he extracted still more short stalks and rubbish till the finished strick came clean and shining as a lock of woman's hair.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000428","text":"From the hanks of long tow he seemed to bring out the tresses like magic.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000429","text":"In his swift hand each strick flashed out from the rough hank with great rapidity, and every crafty, final touch on the teeth made it brighter.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000430","text":"Giving a last flick or two over the small pins, Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000431","text":"Baggs set down his strick and soon a pile of these shining locks grew beside him, while the exhaust sucked away the rubbish and fragments, and the mass of short fibre which he had combed out, also accumulated for future treatment.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000432","text":"He worked with the swiftness and surety of a master craftsman, scourged his tow and snorted sometimes as he struggled with it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000433","text":"He was exerting a tremendous pressure, regulated and applied with skill, and he always exulted in the thought that he, at least, of all the workers performed hand labour far more perfectly than any machine.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000434","text":"But still it was not the least of his many grievances that Government showed too little concern for his comfort.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000435","text":"He was always demanding increased precautions for purifying the air he breathed.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000436","text":"From Mr. Baggs, the long fibre and the short which he had combed out of it, proceeded to the spinning mill; and now a girl came for the stricks he had just created.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000437","text":"Their future under the new master was still on every tongue at Bridetown Mill, and the women turned to the few men who worked among them for information on this paramount subject.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000438","text":"\"No, I ain't heard no more, Sarah,\" answered the hackler to Miss Northover's question. \"You may be sure that those it concerns most will be the last to hear of any changes; and you may also be sure that the changes, when made, will not favour us.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000439","text":"\"You can't tell that,\" answered Sarah, gathering the stricks. \"Old Mrs. Chick, our spreader minder, says the young have always got bigger hearts than the old, and she'd sooner trust them than--\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000440","text":"Mr. Baggs tore a hank through the comb with such vigour that its steel teeth trembled and the dust flew.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000441","text":"\"Tell Granny Chick not to be a bigger fool than God made her,\" he said.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000442","text":"\"The young have got harder hearts than the old, and education, though it may make the head bigger for all I know, makes the heart smaller.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000443","text":"He'll be hard--hard--and I lay a week's wages that he'll get out of his responsibilities by shovelling 'em on his dead father.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000444","text":"\"By letting things be as they are. By saying his father knew best.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000445","text":"\"Young men never think that,\" answered she. \"'Tis well known that no young man ever thought his father knew better than himself.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000446","text":"\"Then he'll pretend to for his own convenience.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000447","text":"\"What about all that talk of changes for the better before Mister Ironsyde died then?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000448","text":"\"Talk of dead men won't go far. We'll hear no more of that.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000449","text":"Sarah frowned and went her way. At the door, however, she turned.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000450","text":"\"I might get to hear something about it next Sunday very like,\" she said.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000451","text":"\"I'm going into Bridport to my Aunt Nelly at 'The Seven Stars'; and she's a great friend of Richard Gurd at 'The Tiger'; and 'tis there Mister Raymond spends half his time, they say.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000452","text":"Gurd may have learned a bit about it.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000453","text":"\"No doubt he'll hear a lot of words, and as for Raymond Ironsyde, his father knew him for a man with a bit of a heart in him and didn't trust him accordingly. But you can take it from me--\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000454","text":"A bell rang and its note struck Mr.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000455","text":"He ceased both to speak and work, dropped his hank, turned down his shirt sleeves and put on his coat.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000456","text":"Sarah at the stroke of the bell also manifested no further interest in Levi's forebodings but left him abruptly.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000457","text":"For it was noon and the dinner-hour had come.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000458","text":"Raymond Ironsyde had spent his life thus far in a healthy and selfish manner.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mental-health","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000459","text":"He owned no objection to hard work of a physical nature, for as a sportsman and athlete he had achieved fame and was jealous to increase it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:nature","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000460","text":"He preserved the perspective of a boy into manhood; while his father waited, not without exasperation, for him to reach adult estate in mind as well as body.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000461","text":"Henry Ironsyde was still waiting when he died and left Raymond to the mercy of Daniel.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000462","text":"Now the brothers had met to thresh out the situation; and a day came when Raymond lunched with his friend and fellow sportsman, Arthur Waldron, of North Hill House, and furnished him with particulars.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000463","text":"In time past, Raymond's grandfather had bought a thousand acres of land on the side of North Hill.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000464","text":"Here he destroyed one old farmhouse and converted another into the country-seat of his family.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000465","text":"He lived and died there; but his son, Henry, cared not for it, and the place had been let to successive tenants for many years.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000466","text":"Waldron was the last of these, and Raymond's ambition had always been some day to return to North Hill House and dwell in his grandfather's home.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000467","text":"At luncheon the party of three sat at a round table on a polished floor of oak. Estelle played hostess and gazed with frank admiration at the chattering visitor. He brought a proposition that made her feel very excited to learn what her father would think of it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000468","text":"He lived out of doors and appeared to be made of iron, for nothing wearied him as yet.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000469","text":"He had high cheek-bones, and a clean-shaved, agreeable face.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000470","text":"He took sport most seriously, was jealous for its rights and observant of its rituals even in the smallest matters.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:leadership","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000471","text":"Upon the etiquette of all field sports he regarded himself, and was regarded, as an arbiter.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000472","text":"\"Tell me how it went,\" he said. \"I hope your brother was sporting?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000473","text":"Waldron used this adjective in the widest possible sense.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000474","text":"It embraced all reputable action and covered virtue.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:stoicism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000475","text":"If conduct were 'sporting,' he demanded no more from any man; while, conversely, 'unsporting' deeds condemned the doer in all relations of life and rendered him untrustworthy from every standpoint.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:relationships","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000476","text":"\"Depends what you call 'sporting,'\" answered Raymond, whose estimate of the word was not so comprehensive.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000477","text":"\"You'd think it would have been rather a case for generosity, but Dan didn't seem to see that.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000478","text":"It's unlucky for me in a way he's not larger-minded.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000479","text":"He's content with justice--what he calls justice.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000480","text":"But justice depends on the mind that's got to do it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000481","text":"There's no finality about it, and what Daniel calls justice, I call beastly peddling, if not actual bullying.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000482","text":"\"And what did he call justice?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000483","text":"\"Well, his first idea was to be just to my father, who was wickedly unjust to me.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000484","text":"That wasn't too good for a start, for if you are going to punish the living, because the dead wanted them to be punished, what price your justice anyway?","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000485","text":"But Daniel had a sort of beastly fairness too, for he recognised that my father's very sudden death must be taken into account.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:justice","theme:love","theme:mortality","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000486","text":"My Aunt Jenny supported me there; and she was sure he would have altered his will if he had had time.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000487","text":"Daniel granted that, and I began to hope I was going to come well out of it; but I counted my chickens before they were hatched.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000488","text":"Some people have a sort of diseased idea of the value of work and seem to think if you don't put ten hours a day into an office, you're not justifying your existence.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000489","text":"Unfortunately for me Daniel is one of those people.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000490","text":"If you don't work, you oughtn't to eat--he actually thinks that.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000491","text":"\"The fallacy is that what seems to be play to a mind like Daniel's, is really seen to be work by a larger mind,\" explained Arthur Waldron.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000492","text":"\"Of course; but I never yet met a merchant who would see it--certainly not Daniel. In fact I've got to work--in his way.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000493","text":"\"D'you mean he's stopping the allowance?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000494","text":"At least he's not renewing it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000495","text":"He's offering me a salary if I'll work.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000496","text":"I can be just to him, though he can't to me.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000497","text":"But, if I'm going to draw the salary, I've got to learn the business and, in fact, go into it and become a spinner.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000498","text":"Then, at the end of five years, if I shine and really get keen about it and help the show, he'll take me into partnership.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000499","text":"That's his offer; and first I told him to go to the devil, and then I changed my mind and, after my aunt had sounded Daniel and found that was his ultimatum, I climbed down.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000500","text":"\"What are you to do? Surely he won't chain an open-air man like you to a wretched desk all your time?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000501","text":"\"So I thought; but he didn't worry about that.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000502","text":"I wanted to go abroad, and combine business with pleasure, and buy the raw material in Russia and India and Italy and so on.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000503","text":"That might have been good enough; but in his rather cold-blooded way, he pointed out that to buy raw material, you wanted to know something about raw material.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000504","text":"He asked me if I knew hemp from flax, and of course I had to say I did not.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000505","text":"I've got to begin where Daniel began ten years ago--at the beginning--with this difference, that I get three hundred quid a year.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000506","text":"In fact there's such a mixture of fairness and unfairness in Daniel's idea that you don't know where to have him.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:justice","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000507","text":"I must live, obviously, and I'd always meant to do something some day.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000508","text":"But naturally my ideas were open air, and I thought when I got things going and took a scheme to my father--for horse-breeding or some useful enterprise--he would have seen I meant business and come round and planked down.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000509","text":"But Daniel has got no use for horse-breeding, so I must be a spinner--for the time anyway.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000510","text":"\"But only girls spin,\" she said. \"You'd never be able to spin, Ray.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000511","text":"\"Everybody's got to spin, it seems,\" he answered.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000512","text":"\"Except the lilies,\" declared Estelle gravely. \"'They toil not, neither do they spin,' you know.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000513","text":"Mr. Waldron regarded his daughter with respect.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000514","text":"\"Just imagine,\" he said, \"at her age. They've made her a member of the Field Botanists' Club. Only eleven years old and invited to join a grown-up club!\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000515","text":"Raymond was somewhat impressed.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000516","text":"\"Fancy a kid like you knowing anything about botany,\" he said.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000517","text":"\"I don't,\" answered the child. \"I'm only just beginning. Why, I haven't mastered the grasses yet. The flowers are easy, of course, but the grasses are ever so difficult.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000518","text":"They returned to Ironsyde's plans.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000519","text":"\"And when d'you weigh in?\" queried his friend.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000520","text":"That's why I invited myself to lunch.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:self-knowledge","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000521","text":"Daniel doesn't want me in the office at Bridport; he wants me here--at Bridetown--so that I can mess about in the works and see a lot of John Best, the foreman, and learn all the practical side of the business.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000522","text":"It seems rather footling work for a man, but he did it; and he says the first thing is to get a personal understanding of the processes and all that.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000523","text":"Of course I've always been keen on machinery.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000524","text":"\"Good, then we shall see something of each other.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000525","text":"\"That's what I want--more than you do, very likely. The idea was that I went to Uncle Ernest, who is willing to let me have a room at 'The Magnolias' and live with him for a year, which is the time Daniel wants me to be here; but I couldn't stick Churchouse for a year.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000526","text":"\"So what do you say? Are you game for a paying guest? You've got tons of room and I shouldn't be in the way.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000527","text":"\"How lovely!\" cried Estelle. \"Do come!\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000528","text":"Arthur Waldron was quietly gratified.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000529","text":"\"I'm sure I should be delighted to have a pal in the house--a kindred spirit, who understands sport. By all means come,\" he said.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:animism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000530","text":"\"You're sure? I should be out most of my time at the blessed works, you know. Could I bring my horse?\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000531","text":"\"That reminds me of one reasonable thing Dan's going to do,\" ran on the other.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000532","text":"I told Aunt Jenny it was no good beginning a new life with a millstone of debts round my neck--in fact we came down to that.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000533","text":"I said it was a vital condition.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000534","text":"Aunt Jenny had rather a lively time between us.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000535","text":"She sympathises with me tremendously, however, and finally got Daniel to promise he would pay off every penny I owed--a paltry two hundred or so.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000536","text":"\"A very sporting arrangement. Make the coffee, Estelle, then we'll take a walk on the downs.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000537","text":"\"I'm going to Uncle Ernest to tea,\" explained Raymond. \"I shall tell him then that I'm not coming to him, thanks to your great kindness.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000538","text":"\"He will be disappointed,\" declared Estelle. \"It seems rather hard of us to take you away from him, I'm afraid.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000539","text":"\"Don't you worry, kiddy. He'll get over it. In fact he'll be jolly thankful, poor old bird. He only did it because he thought he ought to. It's the old, traditional attitude of the Churchouses to the Ironsydes.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:gratitude","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000540","text":"\"He's very wise about church bells, but he's rather vague about flowers,\" replied Estelle. \"He's only interested in dead things, I think; and things that happened long, long ago.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:evening","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:wisdom","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000541","text":"\"In a weird sort of way, a hobby is a man's substitute for sport, I believe,\" said Estelle's father.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000542","text":"\"Many have no feeling for sport; it's left out of them and they seem to be able to live comfortably without it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000543","text":"Instead they develop an instinct for something else.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000544","text":"Generally it's deadly from the sportsman's point of view; but it seems to take the place of sport to the sportless.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000545","text":"How old ruins, or church bells, can supersede a vital, living thing, like the sport of a nation, of course you and I can't explain; but so it is with some minds.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000546","text":"\"It depends how they were brought up,\" suggested Raymond.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000547","text":"\"No--take you; you weren't brought up to sport.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:confucianism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000548","text":"But your own natural, good instinct took you to it.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000549","text":"The moment I saw a ball, I'm told that I shrieked till they gave it to me--at the age of one that was.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000550","text":"And from that time forward they had no trouble with me.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000551","text":"Because a ball, you may say, is the emblem of England's greatness.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000552","text":"I was thinking over it not long ago.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000553","text":"There is not a single game of the first importance that does not depend on a ball.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000554","text":"If one had brains, one could write a book on the inner meaning of that fact.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","theme:solitude","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000555","text":"I believe that the ball has a lot to do with the greatness of the Empire.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000556","text":"\"A jolly good idea. I'll try it on Uncle Ernest,\" promised Raymond.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000557","text":"He was cheerful and depressed in turn.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000558","text":"His company made him happy and the thought that he would come to live at North Hill House also pleased him well; but from time to time the drastic change in his life swept his thoughts like a cloud.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000559","text":"The picture of regular work--unloved work that would enable him to live--struck distastefully upon his mind.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:productivity","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000560","text":"They strolled over North Hill after luncheon and Estelle ran hither and thither, busy with two quests. Her sharp eyes were in the herbage for the flowers and grasses; but she also sought the feathers of the rooks and crows who assembled here in companies.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000561","text":"\"The wing feathers are the best for father's pipes,\" she explained; \"but the tail feathers are also very good.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000562","text":"Sometimes I get splendid luck and find a dozen or two in a morning, and sometimes the birds don't seem to have parted with a single feather.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","audience:morning","language:en","theme:action","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:sufism","tradition:zen"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000563","text":"The place to find them is round the furze clumps, because they catch there when the wind blows them.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000564","text":"The great hogged ridge of North Hill keeps Bridetown snug in winter time, and bursts the snow clouds on its bosom.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000565","text":"To-day the breezes blew and shadows raced above the rolling green expanses.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000566","text":"The downs were broken by dry-built walls and spattered with thickets of furze and white-thorn, black-thorn and elder.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:grief-healing","audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000567","text":"Blue milkwort, buttercups and daisies adorned them, with eye-bright and the lesser, quaking grass that danced over the green.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000568","text":"Rabbits twinkled into the furzes where Waldron's three fox terriers ran before the party; and now and then a brave buck coney would stand upon the nibbled knoll above his burrow and drum danger before he darted in.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:courage","theme:creativity","theme:love","tradition:judaism","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000569","text":"It was a haunt of the cuckoo and peewit, the bunting and carrion crow.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000570","text":"\"Here we killed on the seventeenth of January last,\" said Raymond's host. \"A fine finish to a grand run. We rolled him over on this very spot after forty-five minutes of the best. It is always good to remember great moments in the past.\"","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","theme:mindfulness","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000571","text":"On the southern slope of North Hill there stood a ruined lime-kiln whose walls were full of fern and coated with mother o' thyme.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Divan of Hafiz — Clarke Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000572","text":"Produced by Elaine Walker and the PG Online Distributed Proofreading Team.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000573","text":"THE BOOK OF THREE HUNDRED ANECDOTES.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000574","text":"HISTORICAL, LITERARY, AND HUMOROUS.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000575","text":"BURNS & OATES. LONDON: GRANVILLE MANSIONS. NEW YORK: BARCLAY STREET.","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:action","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000576","text":"Adam, Dr., and the Schoolboy, 106","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000577","text":"Aguesseau, D', Chancellor of France, 115","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000578","text":"Alban's, Duchess of, and the Sailor, 28","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000579","text":"Atterbury, in the House of Peers, 113","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; verify attribution and source citation."},{"id":"hafiz-ext-000580","text":"Bailly, Miss--Escape of the Pretender, 94","author":"Hafiz","source":"Poems from the Divan of Hafiz — Bell Translation","tags":["audience:meditation","language:en","theme:love","tradition:sufism"],"isProverb":false,"isVerified":false,"verificationNote":"Auto-scraped; 